(1, 'a3uud4uxax', 'en', 'article', '', '_self', 'Welcome-to-ApPHP-MicroCMS', 'Welcome to ApPHP MicroCMS!', '<p><strong>PHP MicroCMS</strong> (PHP MCMS) is a simple, but very powerful Content Management System that everyone can use. This script can be installed easily by web developers, webmasters, graphic designers, etc. PHP MCMS was developed in OOP and allows you to <strong>build websites</strong> in a few minutes and then easy <strong>add and edit the content</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>PHP MicroCMS gives possibility for users with very little technical knowledge to build websites and it widely used by our customers due to its easy management tools. PHP MicroCMS requires NO knowledge of HTML, although HTML can be used to enhance the pages by adding headings, images, hyperlinks or simply to emphasize text.</p>\r\n<p>The PHP MCMS is an excellent tool for those who:</p>\r\n<ul class="normal">\r\n<li>Want to create web sites </li>\r\n<li>Look for small, but powerful CMS </li>\r\n<li>Need to build a secure web site quickly </li>\r\n</ul>', 0, '', 'ApPHP MicroCMS', 'php micro cms', 'ApPHP MicroCMS - content management system', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2013-07-28 19:40:34', '0000-00-00', 1, 0, 1, 0, '', 1, '2010-04-22 19:53:44', 'public', 1),
(2, 'a3uud4uxax', 'es', 'article', '', '_self', 'Bienvenido-a-ApPHP-MicroCMS', 'Bienvenido a ApPHP MicroCMS!', 'MicroCMS PHP (PHP MCMS) es un contenido simple, pero muy potente sistema de gestión de que todo el mundo puede utilizar. Este script puede ser instalado fácilmente por los desarrolladores Web, webmasters, diseñadores gráficos, etc PHP MCMS se desarrolló en la programación orientada a objetos y permite crear sitios web en pocos minutos y fácil de añadir y editar contenido.<BR><BR>PHP MicroCMS da la posibilidad para los usuarios con muy poco conocimiento técnico para crear sitios web y es ampliamente utilizado por nuestros clientes debido a sus herramientas de fácil manejo. PHP MicroCMS no requiere ningún conocimiento de HTML, aunque HTML se pueden utilizar para mejorar las páginas por la adición de las partidas, imágenes, enlaces o simplemente para destacar texto.<BR><BR>El MCMS PHP es una excelente herramienta para aquellos que: <UL><LI>Quieres crear sitios web</LI><LI>Puedes buscar pequeño, pero potente CMS</LI><LI>Necesidad de construir un sitio web seguro con rapidez</LI></UL>', 0, '', 'ApPHP MicroCMS', 'php micro cms', 'ApPHP MicroCMS - sistema de gestión de contenidos', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-03-27 12:33:37', '0000-00-00', 1, 0, 1, 0, '', 1, '2010-04-21 19:53:41', 'public', 0),
(3, 'a3uud4uxax', 'de', 'article', '', '_self', 'Willkommen-auf-MicroCMS-ApPHP', 'Willkommen auf MicroCMS ApPHP!', '<P><STRONG>PHP MicroCMS (PHP MCMS)</STRONG> ist ein einfaches, aber sehr leistungsfähiges Content Management System, das jeder benutzen kann. Dieses Skript kann leicht durch Web-Entwickler, Webmaster, Grafiker etc. PHP MCMS in OOP entwickelt wurde und ermöglicht es Ihnen, Webseiten in wenigen Minuten erstellen und dann einfach hinzufügen und bearbeiten die Inhalte eingebaut werden.</P>\\r\\n<P>PHP MicroCMS gibt Möglichkeit für Anwender mit wenig technischem Wissen, um Webseiten zu bauen und es weit von unseren Kunden durch seine einfache Managementtools verwendet. PHP MicroCMS erfordert keine HTML-Kenntnisse, obwohl HTML kann verwendet werden, um die Seiten, indem Überschriften, Bilder, Hyperlinks zu verbessern oder einfach nur, um Text zu betonen.</P>\\r\\n<P>Die PHP-MCMS ist ein ausgezeichnetes Werkzeug für diejenigen, die:</P>\\r\\n<UL>\\r\\n<LI>Wollen Sie Web-Seiten erstellen \\r\\n<LI>Suchen Sie nach kleinen, aber leistungsstarken CMS \\r\\n<LI>Brauchen Sie eine sichere Website schnell aufzubauen</LI></UL>', 0, '', 'ApPHP MicroCMS', 'php micro cms', 'ApPHP MicroCMS - Content Management System', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-03-27 11:25:04', '0000-00-00', 1, 0, 1, 0, '', 1, '2010-04-22 19:53:44', 'public', 1),
(4, 'sdsdsdsdsd', 'es', 'article', '', '_self', 'Instalación-de-PHP-MicroCMS', 'Instalación de PHP MicroCMS', '<DIV class=post>\r\n<H2 id=post-1>Installation of PHP MicroCMS</H2>\r\n<DIV class=storycontent><A name=Installation_of_PHP_MicroCMS></A>\r\n<P>(de la versión 3.0.0 o superior) </P>\r\n<P>A new installation of PHP MicroCMS is a very straight forward process: </P><A name=Step_1._Uncompressing_downloaded_file.></A>\r\n<H3><B>Step 1. Uncompressing downloaded file.</B></H3>\r\n<HR>\r\n\r\n<P>Uncompress the PHP MicroCMS version 3.x.x script archive. The archive will create a directory called "PHPMCMS_3xx" </P>\r\n<P><BR></P><A name=Step_2._Uploading_files.></A>\r\n<H3><B>Step 2. Uploading files.</B></H3>\r\n<HR>\r\n\r\n<P>Upload content of this folder (all files and directories it includes) to your document root (public_html, www, httpdocs etc.) or your micro-cms directory using FTP. Pay attention to DON\\''T use the capital letters in the name of the folder (for Linux users).</P>\r\n<P>For example: </P><PRE>public_html/</PRE>or <PRE>public_html/{micro-cms directory}/</PRE>\r\n<P>Rename default.htaccess into .htaccess if you need to add PHP5 handler.</P>\r\n<P><BR></P><A name=Step_3._Creating_database.></A>\r\n<H3><B>Step 3. Creating database.</B></H3>\r\n<HR>\r\n\r\n<P>Using your hosting Control Panel, phpMyAdmin or another tool, create your database and user, and assign that user to the database. Write down the name of the database, username, and password for the site installation procedure. </P>\r\n<P><BR></P><A name=Step_4._Settings_and_access_rights.></A>\r\n<H3><B>Step 4. Settings and access rights.</B></H3>\r\n<HR>\r\n\r\n<P>4.1. Check access permissions to <B>images/uploads/</B> and <B>wysiwyg/addons/imagelibrary/</B>. You have to set up 755 rights to these folders. Also check if your script is available to change permissions to <B>include/</B> folder. If not - set manually 777 rights to this folder and return them back to 755 after the installation was completed.<BR><BR>4.2. If you run PHP MicroCMS on IIS, you have to allow rewrite mode for Windows. To do this, open the <B>httpd.conf</B> file and uncomment the following lines (remove the trailing #s):<BR><PRE>#LoadModule rewrite_module modules/mod_rewrite.so<BR>#AddModule mod_rewrite.c</PRE>\r\n<P></P>\r\n<P><BR></P><A name=Step_5._Running_install_file.></A>\r\n<H3><B>Step 5. Running install.php file.</B></H3>\r\n<HR>\r\n\r\n<P>Now you can run install.php file. To do this, open a browser and type in Address Bar <PRE>{www.mydomain.com}/install.php</PRE>or <PRE>{www.mydomain.com}/{micro-cms directory}/install.php</PRE>Follow instructions on the screen. You will be asked to enter: database host, database name, username and password. Also you need to enter admin username and admin password, that will be used to get access to administration area of the site. \r\n<P></P>\r\n<P><BR></P><A name=Step_6._Deleting_install_files.></A>\r\n<H3><B>Step 6. Deleting installation files.</B></H3>\r\n<HR>\r\n\r\n<P>After successful installation you will get an appropriate message and warning to remove install.php file and install/ directory. For security reasons, please delete them immediately. </P>\r\n<P><BR></P>Congratulations, you now have PHP MicroCMS v3.x.x. Installed!</DIV></DIV>', 2, 'Instalación', 'ApPHP MicroCMS', 'php micro cms', 'ApPHP MicroCMS - sistema de gestión de contenidos', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-01-15 20:09:43', '0000-00-00', 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'public', 0),
(5, 'sdsdsdsdsd', 'de', 'article', '', '_self', 'Installation-of-PHP-MicroCMS', 'Installation of PHP MicroCMS', '<DIV class=post>\r\n<H2 id=post-1>Installation von PHP MicroCMS</H2>\r\n<DIV class=storycontent><A name=Installation_of_PHP_MicroCMS></A>\r\n<P>(for version 3.0.0 or above)</P>\r\n<P>A new installation of PHP MicroCMS is a very straight forward process:</P><A name=Step_1._Uncompressing_downloaded_file.></A>\r\n<H3><STRONG>Step 1. Uncompressing downloaded file.</STRONG></H3>\r\n<HR>\r\n\r\n<P>Uncompress the PHP MicroCMS version 3.x.x script archive. The archive will create a directory called "PHPMCMS_3xx"</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P><A name=Step_2._Uploading_files.></A>\r\n<H3><STRONG>Step 2. Uploading files.</STRONG></H3>\r\n<HR>\r\n\r\n<P>Upload content of this folder (all files and directories it includes) to your document root (public_html, www, httpdocs etc.) or your micro-cms directory using FTP. Pay attention to DON\\''T use the capital letters in the name of the folder (for Linux users).</P>\r\n<P>For example:</P><PRE>public_html/</PRE>or <PRE>public_html/{micro-cms directory}/</PRE>\r\n<P>Rename default.htaccess into .htaccess if you need to add PHP5 handler.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P><A name=Step_3._Creating_database.></A>\r\n<H3><STRONG>Step 3. Creating database.</STRONG></H3>\r\n<HR>\r\n\r\n<P>Using your hosting Control Panel, phpMyAdmin or another tool, create your database and user, and assign that user to the database. Write down the name of the database, username, and password for the site installation procedure.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P><A name=Step_4._Settings_and_access_rights.></A>\r\n<H3><STRONG>Step 4. Settings and access rights.</STRONG></H3>\r\n<HR>\r\n\r\n<P>4.1. Check access permissions to <STRONG>images/uploads/</STRONG> and <STRONG>wysiwyg/addons/imagelibrary/</STRONG>. You have to set up 755 rights to these folders. Also check if your script is available to change permissions to <STRONG>include/</STRONG> folder. If not - set manually 777 rights to this folder and return them back to 755 after the installation was completed.<BR><BR>4.2. If you run PHP MicroCMS on IIS, you have to allow rewrite mode for Windows. To do this, open the <STRONG>httpd.conf</STRONG> file and uncomment the following lines (remove the trailing #s):</P><PRE>#LoadModule rewrite_module modules/mod_rewrite.so<BR>#AddModule mod_rewrite.c</PRE>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P><A name=Step_5._Running_install_file.></A>\r\n<H3><STRONG>Step 5. Running install.php file.</STRONG></H3>\r\n<HR>\r\n\r\n<P>Now you can run install.php file. To do this, open a browser and type in Address Bar</P><PRE>{www.mydomain.com}/install.php</PRE>or <PRE>{www.mydomain.com}/{micro-cms directory}/install.php</PRE>Follow instructions on the screen. You will be asked to enter: database host, database name, username and password. Also you need to enter admin username and admin password, that will be used to get access to administration area of the site. \r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P><A name=Step_6._Deleting_install_files.></A>\r\n<H3><STRONG>Step 6. Deleting installation files.</STRONG></H3>\r\n<HR>\r\n\r\n<P>After successful installation you will get an appropriate message and warning to remove install.php file and install/ directory. For security reasons, please delete them immediately.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>Congratulations, you now have PHP MicroCMS v3.x.x. Installed!</DIV></DIV>', 3, 'Installation', 'ApPHP MicroCMS', 'php micro cms', 'ApPHP MicroCMS - Content Management System', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-01-12 14:02:06', '0000-00-00', 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'public', 0),
(6, 'sdsdsdsdsd', 'en', 'article', '', '_self', 'Installation-of-PHP-MicroCMS', 'Installation of PHP MicroCMS', '<div class="post">\r\n<h2 id="post-1">Installation of PHP MicroCMS</h2>\r\n<div class="storycontent"><a name="Installation_of_PHP_MicroCMS"></a>\r\n<p>(for version 3.0.0 or above)</p>\r\n<p>A new installation of PHP MicroCMS is a very straight forward process:</p>\r\n<a name="Step_1._Uncompressing_downloaded_file."></a>\r\n<h3><strong>Step 1. Uncompressing downloaded file.</strong></h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Uncompress the PHP MicroCMS version 3.x.x script archive. The archive will create a directory called "PHPMCMS_3xx"</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<a name="Step_2._Uploading_files."></a>\r\n<h3><strong>Step 2. Uploading files.</strong></h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Upload content of this folder (all files and directories it includes) to your document root (public_html, www, httpdocs etc.) or your micro-cms directory using FTP. Pay attention to DON\\''T use the capital letters in the name of the folder (for Linux users).</p>\r\n<p>For example:</p>\r\n<pre>public_html/</pre>\r\nor\r\n<pre>public_html/{micro-cms directory}/</pre>\r\n<p>Rename default.htaccess into .htaccess if you need to add PHP5 handler.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<a name="Step_3._Creating_database."></a>\r\n<h3><strong>Step 3. Creating database.</strong></h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Using your hosting Control Panel, phpMyAdmin or another tool, create your database and user, and assign that user to the database. Write down the name of the database, username, and password for the site installation procedure.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<a name="Step_4._Settings_and_access_rights."></a>\r\n<h3><strong>Step 4. Settings and access rights.</strong></h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>4.1. Check access permissions to <strong>images/uploads/</strong> and <strong>wysiwyg/addons/imagelibrary/</strong>. You have to set up 755 rights to these folders. Also check if your script is available to change permissions to <strong>include/</strong> folder. If not - set manually 777 rights to this folder and return them back to 755 after the installation was completed.<br /><br />4.2. If you run PHP MicroCMS on IIS, you have to allow rewrite mode for Windows. To do this, open the <strong>httpd.conf</strong> file and uncomment the following lines (remove the trailing #s):</p>\r\n<pre>#LoadModule rewrite_module modules/mod_rewrite.so<br />#AddModule mod_rewrite.c</pre>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<a name="Step_5._Running_install_file."></a>\r\n<h3><strong>Step 5. Running install.php file.</strong></h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Now you can run install.php file. To do this, open a browser and type in Address Bar</p>\r\n<pre>{www.mydomain.com}/install.php</pre>\r\nor\r\n<pre>{www.mydomain.com}/{micro-cms directory}/install.php</pre>\r\nFollow instructions on the screen. You will be asked to enter: database host, database name, username and password. Also you need to enter admin username and admin password, that will be used to get access to administration area of the site.\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<a name="Step_6._Deleting_install_files."></a>\r\n<h3><strong>Step 6. Deleting installation files.</strong></h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>After successful installation you will get an appropriate message and warning to remove install.php file and install/ directory. For security reasons, please delete them immediately.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\nCongratulations, you now have PHP MicroCMS v3.x.x. Installed!</div>\r\n</div>', 1, 'Installation', 'ApPHP MicroCMS', 'php micro cms', 'ApPHP MicroCMS - content management system', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2013-07-28 19:40:13', '0000-00-00', 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'public', 0),
